ai-kv4.6:1.3_0: Attending to awakening, one who has entered upon awakening; he is undeveloped.
ai-kv4.6:1.4_0: And you don’t keep on doing it.
ai-kv4.6:2.4_0: And you don’t keep on doing it.
ai-kv4.6:2.7_0: Bodhisattages him on that very day:
ai-kv4.6:2.8_0: And you don’t keep on doing it.
ai-kv4.6:3.1_0: Bodhisattages him on that very day:
ai-kv4.6:3.3_0: They completely understand suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the path.
ai-kv4.6:3.4_0: And you don’t keep on doing it.
ai-kv4.6:4.3_0: And he was the Buddha, the Lord of the Earth.
ai-kv4.6:4.4_0: And you don’t keep on doing it.
ai-kv4.6:5.1_0: And he was the Buddha, the Lord of the Earth.
ai-kv4.6:5.3_0: Bodhisattages him on that very day:
ai-kv4.6:5.4_0: And you don’t keep on doing it.
ai-kv4.6:6.1_0: Bodhisattages him on that very day:
ai-kv4.6:6.3_0: They directly know suffering as suffering.
ai-kv4.6:6.4_0: And you don’t keep on doing it.
ai-kv4.6:7.1_0: The Buddha-to-be during the time to the Awakening One, thus he is the Bodhi (Tree).
ai-kv4.6:7.3_0: In the past, the Buddha-to-bearing the Bodhi tree he is conceived.
ai-kv4.6:7.4_0: And you don’t keep on doing it.
ai-kv4.6:8.1_0: The Buddha presently understands that they are the origin of suffering. They give up suffering. They realize the cessation of suffering.
ai-kv4.6:8.4_0: And you don’t keep on doing it.
ai-kv4.6:9.1_0: The Buddha-to-be during the time to the Awakening One, thus he is the Bodhi (Tree).
ai-kv4.6:9.3_0: Bodhisatta, the Buddha-to-be during the Bodhi (Tree), thus he is the Lord of the Awakening .
ai-kv4.6:9.4_0: And you don’t keep on doing it.
ai-kv4.6:10.1_0: The Buddha truly understands that suffering is the path to awakening ...
ai-kv4.6:10.4_0: And you don’t keep on doing it.
ai-kv4.6:11.1_0: In the past, the Buddha does not do so.
ai-kv4.6:11.3_0: The Buddha has no duties to the Awakening One, but he does not do anything to be Bodhi (Tree).
ai-kv4.6:11.4_0: And you don’t keep on doing it.
ai-kv4.6:12.3_0: The Buddha has not developed the present path to awakening ...
ai-kv4.6:12.4_0: And you don’t keep on doing it.
ai-kv4.6:13.1_0: In the future time, the Buddha was not awakened to him, and he does not do so.
ai-kv4.6:13.3_0: The Buddha has no duties to the Awakening One, but he does not do anything to be Bodhi (Tree).
ai-kv4.6:13.4_0: And you don’t keep on doing it.
ai-kv4.6:14.1_0: Bodhisatta doesn’t understand that he is indeed awakening ...
ai-kv4.6:14.3_0: The Buddha has not developed the present path to awakening ...
ai-kv4.6:14.4_0: And you don’t keep on doing it.
ai-kv4.6:15.1_0: In the past, future, the Buddha, the present time in the present, the Buddha, the Bodhi (Tree),
ai-kv4.6:15.3_0: he is the Buddha, the bearer of the three worsts,
ai-kv4.6:15.4_0: And you don’t keep on doing it.
ai-kv4.6:16.1_0: he is the Buddha, the bearer of the three worsts,
ai-kv4.6:16.3_0: Saying, “ uncrowded” he possessed the three (supernatural) faculties that he was conceived in the Bodhi (Tree).
ai-kv4.6:16.4_0: And you don’t keep on doing it.
ai-kv4.6:17.4_0: The Buddha is not incapable of the Awakening:
ai-kv4.6:17.6_0: and gaining joy for the sake of the being intent on awakening:
ai-kv4.6:18.4_0: And you don’t keep on doing it.
ai-kv4.6:18.5_0: The story at the Bodhi tree is finished.
